The paper deals with an online decision problem, which is a common topic in the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves learning values from known distributions, which suggests information theory (cs.IT) as another likely subfield. The paper also discusses the performance of algorithms in the presence of correlations, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The use of threshold-based algorithms and the concept of robustness suggest game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) as additional possible subfields.
